  "topic": "PLANT",
  "explanation": "A flower is an integral reproductive part of many types of plants, specifically flowering plants (angiosperms). While not all plants produce flowers (e.g., ferns, mosses, conifers), for those that do, the flower is responsible for producing seeds and fruits, essential for the plant's propagation and life cycle. Therefore, a flower is a specialized structure found on a plant."
}
